				K just finished this qust.  For such a simple quest it is very confusig.  The ques IS i repeat IS brokenas of the last update.  In kalamdim thee is a dwarf named bloodforge in the warrior's guild.  Hey is SUPPOSE to give the quest however they have re-programmed hm for the runny-eye warbeads quest.  However you can still obtain he ammer as i did.  Go to Quenos out by the docks to a place named Fishes ale. Buy som honeymeadand hail trumpy irontoe.  Question him on what he says and he will walk to a sacluded place near the arena entrance.  DO NOT atack him in the bar or you will be kos by corrupt guards and the bar bouncer who both hit for 50-80 damage.  Kill him when he gets to the arena.  There are no guards patroling in this area except for one who is NOT corrupt i repeat NOT corrupt.  Get someone to root him as he can make quite a dash for a fat lil dwarf to his protectors.  Kill him and get back to kalamdim.  Make SURE you have amiable, warmly or better with the gurds.  If you dont do the one-chip quest or the goblin beads quest to earn faction.  Take the head you looted off of irontoe an give it to Bloodforge.  He will then give u the hammer.  It is 13 damage, 2hb, 10 magic sv, 50 attack delay.  Sells for about 30pp on my sever. As i sai after petitioning a GM he tod me the quest is BROKEN ad verent has not made an ttempt as of te last update to fix it.  hoever if u give himthe head you will get the hammer noting that you have good faction with storguard.  Ok here are some commen mistakes that i see people make.  1) there is antoher bloodforge out in bb near thecrossrods.  This is NOT the boodforge to give the hammer to.  2) People attack irontoe in the bar in quenos.  NOT  a good idea.  3)Once you kill irontoe once in the bar youwill be KOS by the bouncer from then on.  4) There is another irontoe that lives in Kalamdim named Tumpy, this is NOT the irontoe you want to kill.  5) Turning in the hammer w/o good faction after all your work will lead to &quot;I accept your generous offer&quot; and nothing in return.  :(  I know from experience.  OK that solved ou will do fine on this quest good luck to you!
